  "prompt": "How much the rubber expansion joint cost ?",
  "response": "The cost of a rubber expansion joint can vary widely depending on several factors such as:\n\n1. **Size/Diameter**: Larger joints typically cost more.\n2. **Material**: Different rubber compounds (e.g., EPDM, neoprene, nitrile) have different costs.\n3. **Pressure and Temperature Ratings**: Higher-rated joints are more expensive.\n4. **Design and Configuration**: Simple joints are cheaper than complex ones with flanges, liners, or multiple arches.\n5. **Quantity**: Bulk purchases may reduce the per-unit cost.\n6. **Brand and Supplier**: Prices can vary between manufacturers and distributors.\n\nAs a rough estimate:\n- **Small joints (1-2 inches)**: $20\u2013$100\n- **Medium joints (4-6 inches)**: $100\u2013$300\n- **Large joints (8-12 inches)**: $300\u2013$800 or more\n\nFor accurate pricing, it\u2019s best to contact suppliers like **Trelleborg**, **Proco Products**, **Garlock**, or local distributors and provide them with your specific requirements.",
